<div id="tab_plugin_lazarus" class="tab-pane">
    <div class="container-fluid lazarus-ui">
        <div class="lazarus-hero">
            <div class="lazarus-title-stack">
                <h3 class="lazarus-title">Lazarus</h3>
                <p class="lazarus-tagline">
                    Resumes failed prints. If the print is still on the bed, with Lazarus it is not dead... only sleeping.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="lazarus-nav-row">
                <div class="lazarus-nav-left">
                    <button class="btn lazarus-nav-btn"
                            type="button"
                            data-bind="click: openActivationPage"
                            title="Open activation and pricing in your browser.">
                        Activate
                    </button>

                    <button class="btn lazarus-nav-btn"
                            type="button"
                            data-toggle="modal"
                            data-target="#howto-modal"
                            title="Open a quick workflow guide.">
                        How It Works
                    </button>

                    <button class="btn lazarus-nav-btn"
                            type="button"
                            data-toggle="modal"
                            data-target="#contact-modal"
                            title="Open support details.">
                        Contact
                    </button>
                </div>

                <div class="lazarus-nav-right">
                    <span class="label label-success"
                          data-bind="visible: licenseValid()">
                        License Valid
                    </span>

                    <span class="label label-important"
                          data-bind="visible: !licenseValid()">
                        License Required
                    </span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lazarus-help-text"
             data-bind="visible: !licenseValid()">
            Pricing and activation happen on the Lazarus website, outside OctoPrint.
        </div>

        <div class="lazarus-card lazarus-mode-card">
            <div class="lazarus-mode-copy">
                <div class="lazarus-standard-label">Printer Control Mode</div>
                <h4>Motion Command Path</h4>
                <p class="lazarus-help-text">
                    Use standard OctoPrint motion commands, or switch to Moonraker / Klipper mode for printers controlled through Moonraker.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="lazarus-mode-controls">
                <button class="btn lazarus-toggle-btn"
                        type="button"
                        data-bind="click: toggleControlMode, css: { 'is-enabled': moonrakerMode() }"
                        title="Switch between OctoPrint mode and Moonraker / Klipper mode.">
                    Moonraker / Klipper:
                    <span class="lazarus-mode-state"
                          data-bind="text: moonrakerModeLabel, css: { 'is-enabled': moonrakerMode() }"></span>
                </button>

                <button class="btn lazarus-moonraker-test-btn"
                        type="button"
                        data-bind="click: testMoonraker, visible: moonrakerMode"
                        title="Verify that Moonraker and Klippy are reachable.">
                    Test Connection
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lazarus-card">
            <div class="lazarus-inputs-head">
                <h4>Source File</h4>

                <div class="lazarus-file-selector">
                    <div class="lazarus-file-selector-label">Selected file</div>

                    <div class="lazarus-file-selected"
                         data-bind="text: selectedFileLabel"
                         title="Currently selected G-code source."></div>

                    <div class="lazarus-file-selector-controls">
                        <select class="input-block-level lazarus-input"
                                data-bind="
                                    options: availableFiles,
                                    optionsText: 'label',
                                    optionsValue: 'path',
                                    value: selectedServerFilePath,
                                    optionsCaption: 'Choose OctoPrint file',
                                    event: { change: selectServerFile }
                                "
                                title="Choose a G-code file from OctoPrint local storage."></select>

                        <button class="btn lazarus-function-btn lazarus-file-picker-btn"
                                type="button"
                                data-bind="click: openLocalFilePicker"
                                title="Choose a G-code file from this device.">
                            Choose From Device
                        </button>
                    </div>

                    <div class="lazarus-file-dropzone"
                         data-bind="css: { 'is-dragging': isDraggingFile() }"
                         title="Drag and drop a G-code file here.">
                        Drag and drop a `.gcode` file here
                    </div>

                    <input id="lazarus-local-file-input"
                           type="file"
                           accept=".gcode,.gco,.gc,.g"
                           class="lazarus-hidden-file-input">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row-fluid">
                <div class="span6">
                    <label>Measured Print Height (mm)</label>

                    <input type="number"
                           step="0.1"
                           class="input-block-level lazarus-input"
                           placeholder="22.0"
                           data-bind="value: measuredHeight"
                           title="Measure the saved print and enter the lower of the two edge measurements.">
                </div>

                <div class="span6">
                    <label>Alignment Side</label>

                    <select class="input-block-level lazarus-input"
                            data-bind="value: alignmentSide"
                            title="Choose the side that measured lower.">
                        <option value="left">Left</option>
                        <option value="right">Right</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lazarus-help-text">
                Layer height is detected automatically from the selected G-code file.
            </div>

            <button class="btn btn-large btn-block lazarus-action-btn"
                    data-bind="click: buildResume, enable: licenseValid() && !buildInProgress()"
                    title="Generate a resume file and the alignment target.">
                Build Resume G-code
            </button>
        </div>

        <div class="lazarus-card" data-bind="visible: buildInProgress() || resumeBuilt()">
            <div class="lazarus-warning-box">
                <div class="lazarus-warning-intro" data-bind="visible: buildInProgress()">
                    Building your resume file. This may take a few seconds.
                </div>

                <p>Use Safe Resume Homing unless you already trust the printer's current coordinates or a saved assumed position.</p>
                <p>After that, move to the true alignment point and use OctoPrint's motion controls to align the nozzle to the chosen edge of the print.</p>
                <p>When the nozzle is aligned, click Position Calibrated to lock coordinates and add a safe Z hop before heating the nozzle.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lazarus-card" data-bind="visible: resumeBuilt()">
            <div class="lazarus-stage-header">
                <h4>Calibration</h4>

                <div class="lazarus-datum-display"
                     title="The target point used for final alignment.">
                    True Alignment Point:
                    <span>X=<strong data-bind="text: datumX"></strong></span>
                    <span>Y=<strong data-bind="text: datumY"></strong></span>
                    <span>Z=<strong data-bind="text: datumZ"></strong></span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row-fluid">
                <div class="span6">
                    <button class="btn btn-block lazarus-function-btn"
                            data-bind="click: openSafeResumeHomingPrompt"
                            title="Choose the safest way to establish a starting coordinate state.">
                        1. Safe Resume Homing
                    </button>
                </div>

                <div class="span6">
                    <button class="btn btn-block lazarus-function-btn"
                            data-bind="click: goToDatum"
                            title="Move the toolhead over the alignment target.">
                        2. Move To Alignment Point
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lazarus-card" data-bind="visible: resumeBuilt()">
            <h4>Resume G-code Preview</h4>

            <pre class="lazarus-preview"
                 data-bind="visible: resumeBuilt(), text: previewText"></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="lazarus-card lazarus-resume-card">
            <label class="checkbox lazarus-checkbox">
                <input type="checkbox"
                       data-bind="checked: motionAcknowledged">
                I have aligned the toolhead, confirmed temperatures, and it is safe to move.
            </label>

            <div class="lazarus-resume-actions">
                <button class="btn btn-large lazarus-download-btn"
                        data-bind="enable: canDownloadResume(), click: downloadResume"
                        title="Download the generated resume G-code.">
                    Download Resume G-code
                </button>

                <button class="btn btn-large lazarus-resume-btn"
                        data-bind="enable: canResume(), click: resumeNow"
                        title="Start the generated resume sequence.">
                    Resume Print
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lazarus-legal-links">
            <a href="https://app.lazarus3dprint.com/license" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">License</a>
            <span aria-hidden="true">|</span>
            <a href="https://app.lazarus3dprint.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Terms</a>
            <span aria-hidden="true">|</span>
            <a href="https://app.lazarus3dprint.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Privacy</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="safe-resume-homing-modal"
         class="modal hide fade"
         tabindex="-1"
         role="dialog"
         aria-labelledby="safe-resume-homing-modal-label"
         aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h3 id="safe-resume-homing-modal-label">Safe Resume Homing</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-body">
            <div class="lazarus-option-stack">
                <label class="checkbox lazarus-checkbox lazarus-expert-option"
                       title="Use this only if your printer still has trustworthy coordinates.">
                    <input type="checkbox" data-bind="checked: attestCurrentCoordinates">
                    My printer already has a trustworthy current coordinate state.
                </label>

                <label class="checkbox lazarus-checkbox lazarus-expert-option"
                       title="Use saved assumed position values from the Lazarus settings.">
                    <input type="checkbox" data-bind="checked: useAssumedPositionCoordinates">
                    Use saved assumed position coordinates.
                </label>

                <div class="lazarus-datum-display"
                     title="Saved assumed position coordinates from the settings panel.">
                    Saved Assumed Position:
                    <span>X=<strong data-bind="text: parkX"></strong></span>
                    <span>Y=<strong data-bind="text: parkY"></strong></span>
                    <span>Z=<strong data-bind="text: parkZ"></strong></span>
                </div>

                <div class="lazarus-standard-option">
                    <div class="lazarus-standard-label">Default option</div>
                    <button class="btn btn-large btn-block lazarus-action-btn"
                            type="button"
                            data-bind="click: applySafeResumeHoming"
                            title="Set a temporary Z and home X and Y.">
                        Run Safe Resume Homing
                    </button>
                    <p class="lazarus-disclaimer">
                        Best choice for most cartesian and CoreXY printers when you need a reliable starting state.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" type="button" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="alignment-step-modal"
         class="modal hide fade"
         tabindex="-1"
         role="dialog"
         aria-labelledby="alignment-step-modal-label"
         aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h3 id="alignment-step-modal-label">Precision Alignment</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-body">
            <p class="lazarus-critical-warning">
                <strong>Important:</strong> Do not use Z-offset tools for this step. Use normal motion controls and align the nozzle to the selected edge of the print with paper-test clearance.
            </p>

            <div class="lazarus-failsafe-row">
                <button class="btn lazarus-failsafe-btn"
                        type="button"
                        data-bind="click: resetAlignmentZ"
                        title="Reset the temporary Z coordinate if you need more room to align safely.">
                    Need more room to align Z?
                </button>
            </div>

            <div class="lazarus-calibrated-action">
                <p class="lazarus-disclaimer">When X, Y, and Z are aligned to the print, lock the position and add a safe Z hop.</p>
                <button class="btn btn-large btn-block lazarus-action-btn"
                        type="button"
                        data-bind="click: lockDatum"
                        title="Lock the calibrated position and raise Z by the configured safe hop.">
                    Position Calibrated
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" type="button" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="howto-modal"
         class="modal hide fade"
         tabindex="-1"
         role="dialog"
         aria-labelledby="howto-modal-label"
         aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h3 id="howto-modal-label">How It Works</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-body">
            <p>1. Select the original G-code file and enter the measured height of the saved print.</p>
            <p>2. Build the resume file to calculate the true alignment point.</p>
            <p>3. Establish a safe starting coordinate state, then move to the alignment point.</p>
            <p>4. Use OctoPrint motion controls to align the nozzle to the print and click Position Calibrated.</p>
            <p>5. Confirm temperatures, then download the resume file or start the resume sequence.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" type="button" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="contact-modal"
         class="modal hide fade"
         tabindex="-1"
         role="dialog"
         aria-labelledby="contact-modal-label"
         aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h3 id="contact-modal-label">Contact</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-body">
            <p>Support and activation: <a href="https://app.lazarus3dprint.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">app.lazarus3dprint.com</a></p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:ksmith1489@protonmail.com">ksmith1489@protonmail.com</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" type="button" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
